1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Mum...

2
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You stopped Malika from going to university?

3
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Yes.

4
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Because I don't trust her anymore.

5
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She's very upset.

6
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I know.

7
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She's upset that her Aunt's coming.

8
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Do you think she'd give in if you forced her?

9
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She's been engaged to him for years. I've just got to convince her for the marriage.

10
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I don't think she'd give in.

11
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Wake Her Majesty up. Tell her breakfast's ready.

12
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm taking it to her room. I don't think she's coming out today.

13
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Okay. Keep it there even if she refuses.

14
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
So that she knows we don't care if she refuses anything. Anything, get it?

15
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Yes.

16
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Here's your breakfast.

17
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
No thanks. Take it back.

18
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Hello? I said something.

19
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Mum told me to keep it here even if you refused.

20
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Oh?

21
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She wants me to know she doesn't care, right?

22
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You're upset because Aunt's coming, right?

23
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
No. I'm upset because Mum's invited her!

24
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You've been engaged. You'll get married to him soon.

25
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Engaged? I don't accept it!

26
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Everyone else does.

27
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And who do you think could be better than Asim?

28
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why?

29
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What've I done to deserve someone like Asim?

30
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Please don't say that. It angers the Lord.

31
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
No idea why Dad named me Malika [Empress]!

32
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
For all that barbarism, I'm sure he would've named you Anne Bonny!

33
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Ha ha ha, get this vaudeville outta here, or you're getting a proper pasting!

34
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Malika, my dear... Please get this hatred for Asim out of you.

35
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
He loves you so much. He'll take care of you!

36
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Gordon Bennett! You know everything!

37
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You're quite the diviner! Go and ask Mum to put up a board outside. 'Zahida the Augurer'! 'We tell girls in the mire their destiny'!

38
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Let me be very clear - my dreams begin where Asim's end!

39
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Don't you realise you're driving a wedge between Mum and Aunt?
-So I should take the fall! You can't be serious!

40
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Who'd you marry if not Asim?

41
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm sure there's someone the Lord would've destined for me...

42
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Aye, but you're not ready to marry him.

43
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Shut your gob! Take this breakfast and get out!

44
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Can't you hear me? Take it back!

45
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Growing insolent every day!

46
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I was thinking...

47
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Yeah?

48
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm going to Dubai for work.

49
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What?

50
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What about me? If you're not here...

51
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Just let me finish.

52
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I think it'll be fabulous if you came with me.

53
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Me?

54
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Yeah.

55
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It'll do you good to go somewhere for a change.

56
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
No way.

57
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why?

58
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You know I don't want to stand in your way.

59
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You know it hurts me when you say that.

60
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I want to tour the world with you.

61
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Dubai's just the beginning.

62
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Okay...

63
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But we aren't really... You know...

64
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
We can't go out together until we take things forward.

65
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You're the only one stopping things from going forward.

66
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Just leave it, will you?

67
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Do you know what's the best time for me?

68
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
When I'm with you.

69
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Like right now.

70
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm having my best time.

71
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
How smooth...

72
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Well, at least say yes to this...

73
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Yes? What is it?

74
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Take the bike. Use it.

75
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I can't.

76
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
My family asks me so many things if I do.

77
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I've got two sisters who haven't been married yet.

78
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I worry more for them than roaming around on a bike.

79
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You're right...

80
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You've got a lot of responsibility.

81
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But we're together... I'm sure we can solve any problems that come up.

82
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Trust God.

83
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Okay?

84
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And leave your bike here if your family asks about it.

85
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Keep the keys. Use it when you like.

86
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Yes?

87
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Thank you.

88
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Sure you're not coming to Dubai? Oh, I was just kidding.

89
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Please don't mind my asking, but you said Malika doesn't want to get married a few days back. How'd you convince her so quickly?

90
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Aqil thought she should get married. She can continue studying from over there.

91
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But why? Didn't you always oppose him?

92
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Because you're not well.

93
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Please. Don't let emotions make you take a decision which could cost Asim and Malika later.

94
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Don't you want Malika to be your daughter-in-law?
-What are you saying?

95
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You know I was so delighted at the engagement! More importantly, you know how much my son loves her! Despite all her bitterness and spite!

96
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
So, what's your problem?
-Aunt...

97
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
We need to talk.

98
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Go in!

99
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
We're talking about something important.

100
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It's my future you're deciding. I have a right to speak!

101
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Yes? Go on.

102
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Mum thinks I'll run off with someone if I went to university.

103
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But they don't know that one could run off on the day of the wedding.

104
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Mind your tongue!

105
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
All I want to say is... If you tried to force me, you better be prepared to never see my face again!

106
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I wish He'd never given me someone like her...

107
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Don't worry. You won't have to do anything of the sort because of Asim.

108
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It's up to you.

109
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Hello, Aunt! What a pleasant surprise!

110
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Hello! How are you?

111
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What's up with her?

112
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Nothing. Just a bit worried about Malika.

113
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I've told her not to worry about anything.

114
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Everything will be taken care of. Just fix the date.

115
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
We're not ready for the marriage just yet.

116
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
We're not fixing the date until she's done with her studies.

117
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But you said it yourself, Aunt...

118
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It occurred to me it'd disturb Malika if we got about with the wedding and all...

119
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Okay, then.

120
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm sure you would've thought about it...

121
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Mum... Ask Munni to get me some black coffee.

122
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Okay.

123
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Alright, I'll go change. Take care.

124
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Salma...

125
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why didn't you tell Aqil?

126
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'd rather keep it between us.

127
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Aqil's a man... Malika's brother. He wouldn't be able to take it if he heard what she said.

128
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It can't be hidden for long...

129
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
May the Lord guide her... I won't tell Asim how much the love of his life despises him either.

130
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And... Let destiny unfold...

131
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Asim?

132
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Everything alright? You look worried.

133
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm good. Everything's okay.

134
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Are you sure?

135
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Yeah. All good.

136
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Hello?

137
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Hello.

138
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Who is it?

139
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You're the only girl I ever gave my visiting card.

140
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But you ask me who I am?

141
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It's you!

142
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm sorry but I didn't save your number.

143
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I wasn't expecting that.

144
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Anyway...

145
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I want to meet you.

146
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Haven't you thought about it long enough?

147
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You don't get such a chance twice.

148
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
People long to get a chance all their lives...

149
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I don't get it.
-That's why I want to meet you.

150
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'll tell you everything you need to know.

151
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I can also pick you up if you want.

152
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'll let you know.

153
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Quickly.

154
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Your luck's in but it may be out any moment.

155
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Sir?

156
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Bye.

157
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But how'd he get my number?

158
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Well, what do I care?

159
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I told them we're in no hurry.

160
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Malika can finish her education.

161
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Was she at home?

162
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Yeah.

163
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Aqil's said she can only go to university after her marriage.

164
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Blimey, the twit...

165
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Sometimes, the most unexpected people can be the most wise.

166
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What is it?

167
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What's happened?

168
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It's not like they'd tell us.

169
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Remember - nobody would tell what's up with their daughters.

170
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Mum...

171
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why do I feel there's something you're not telling me?

172
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You deserve better, Asim.

173
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Did she refuse?

174
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You ask as if you hope she won't.

175
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I hope you had no trouble finding your way.

176
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Of course, Aunt. I used the map.

177
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You could've asked Waqas to pick you up.

178
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I didn't want to disturb him.

179
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm sure he would've loved to.

180
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You're right, Aunt, but I don't like to depend on someone so much.

181
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Okay. I get it...

182
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But we're here for you. Let us know if you need anything.

183
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Thank you, that's really sweet of you.

184
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You could've brought Faizan along.

185
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
He left for work. He had a meeting.
-Oh...

186
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Hey!

187
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Hey!

188
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What a surprise! How are you?

189
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Very well. How are you?

190
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Great. Never been better! You look nice.

191
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You look awesome as well!

192
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
How'd you come here?
-On my own.

193
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
On you own? You drove all the way?

194
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Yeah, what are you so intrigued about?

195
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Aunt was surprised too.

196
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Because you mentioned the traffic here...

197
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Nothing's impossible.

198
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I even said I'll find my way!

199
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You could've told me.

200
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Hear that?

201
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You just need to ask.

202
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I've got to take this call. I'll be back.

203
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Know what?

204
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Mum never talks to me so softly.

205
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Aren't you always fishing for sympathies?

206
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I know she loves you so much.

207
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
How say you love me too... A bit?

208
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Bli --

209
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why, is it --

210
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Wait a minute.

211
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Hey, buddy, what's up?

212
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Hi.

213
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I was coming over. I thought I'd check.

214
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm home, but busy.

215
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What do you mean?

216
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
We've got guests.

217
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Who are you kidding?

218
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Just say Novera's there.

219
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Alright, see you at the gym in the evening.

220
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Bye.
-Bye.

221
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Sorry. One of the lads.

222
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why'd you say no? I was about to leave.

223
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But why?

224
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
No way, you're not allowed to go. Not just yet.

225
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm sure Mum would rather you have lunch...

226
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Absolutely. No one's going out. I've prepared your favourite Thai dish.

227
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Thank you, Aunt.
-We're having lunch together, okay?

228
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Just perfect!
-Thank you, very sweet of you!

229
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Where are you going?

230
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm coming in a minute!
-Okay.

231
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
So...

232
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I talked to Mr Atif...

233
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
He says I should be thinking about your marriage.

234
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Atif said that?

235
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Of course.

236
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I just meant -- What's Atif got to do with my marriage?

237
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
He's divorced his own wife, set himself free... And worrying about my marriage!

238
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What's up with him? I'll talk to him.

239
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Don't you dare!

240
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Don't you dare say a word to Mr Atif!

241
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why?

242
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
We've got no right to talk about his personal life.

243
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
If Atif cares about my marriage so much, he should give me a room here.

244
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I wouldn't keep my wife in this servant's quarters in the basement, after all!

245
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why?

246
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
If your Mum can live here, why can't your wife?

247
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Mum...

248
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Not everyone settles for small things like you...

249
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Well, Noriyan, life would be too difficult with anyone who doesn't.

250
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She's very nice, Mum.

251
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Mum...

252
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
If you met her, you'd realise she's all I need to light up my life.

253
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
So Mr Atif was right!

254
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What?

255
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Don't you like your Uncle's daughters?

256
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Uncle's daughters?

257
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
No, Mum, I like someone else!

258
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What about her?

259
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She can't live without me.

260
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
A fellow student?

261
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Yes.

262
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I want to take you to her.

263
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Please tell me you're coming.

264
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Once I'm back from the village, okay.

265
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Thank you, Mum!

266
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Honestly, though...

