276
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Yeah. Not counting the maid who lives here, yeah.

277
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But don't worry.

278
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She's a servant.

279
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She lives on my money.

280
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She's got a son, too...

281
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm supporting him too.

282
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I told you...

283
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You have no right to say anything about Mr Atif's life.

284
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Better stay quiet.

285
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Okay.

286
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Sorry.

287
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Turn off the pool filter, get it covered. Do something about the mover or there will be flooding. And keep the bags in the car. Not this --
-Okay.

288
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Good evening.
-Good evening.
-Blimey, Zahir!

289
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Where've you been?

290
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
No call, no text...

291
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Mum's back from London. I was busy with her.

292
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Oh... I totally forgot! Why didn't you tell me?

293
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What else do I have to tell you? And for how long?

294
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What is it?

295
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Angry with me?

296
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why would I be?

297
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You didn't even bother to call and ask me where I am or how I'm doing, or what I've been up to... For three days!

298
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You know what I'm like... Forgetful, messy...

299
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You weren't this way. But you're staying this way.

300
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You shouldn't be saying that. Come.

301
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Let's go see Aunt.

302
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Mum's not home. She's gone for lunch with friends.

303
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
So that's why you're here. Okay.

304
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm here to tell you I'll be joining you in Dubai two days later.

305
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What?

306
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why?

307
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But you were so excited about the Dubai distribution!
-I know. I was excited, wanted to come and all...

308
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But something's come up.

309
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Anyway, I've talked to the folks over there, they'll take care of everything without me.

310
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'll take care of everything else when I get there.

311
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Look after yourself, I'm off. Bye.

312
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But -- Hey -- Zahir -- Za --!

313
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What's up with him?

314
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
At least ask Mum!
-She ain't even talking to me!

315
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Do you think she'd talk to you if you had your way like this?

316
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I have to go, Munni.

317
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Okay, have your breakfast.

318
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
No way, I'm late!

319
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It's ready!

320
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'll miss the bus!
-Let her go.

321
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
If she missed her 'bus', we'll regret it the rest of our lives.

322
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I have to go, Mum.

323
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'll tell you everything when I'm back.

324
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Should I get breakfast, Mum?

325
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Hello!

326
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Come, I'll drop you.

327
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I don't need any favours from anyone.

328
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It's no favour, Malika. I want to talk about something.

329
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What is it?

330
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I want to tell you something.

331
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I've already told Aunt all I have to say about it.

332
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You could've just honoured my love...

333
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Mum always thought you hated me and you proved her right.

334
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Believe it if you still can't.

335
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And you better not stand in my way like that again.

336
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Mr Asim!

337
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
The boss is calling you.

338
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm coming.

339
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Ayesha, please email these.

340
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
May I come in, sir?

341
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Yes.

342
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Good morning.

343
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
'Morning.

344
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You wanted to talk about something?

345
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Yes sir. I heard there are a few openings in marketing. I wanted to talk about that.

346
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Yeah. A few people left the job... Know someone you can recommend?

347
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Yes, sir. My cousin. He's done a BA.

348
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm sure he's got some experience?

349
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
No, sir. He doesn't have any experience.

350
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But I'm sure he'll do well. He works really hard.

351
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
He isn't really qualified for this job... But I trust your judgement.

352
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Bring him tomorrow. I'd like to meet him.

353
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Thank you, sir. I'm on it.

354
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Good. You may go.

355
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What's his problem?

356
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Yeah, Asim?

357
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm sorry, were you sleeping?

358
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Did you call to ask that?

359
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
No, I called to tell you that I've talked to my boss.

360
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
He's called you for an interview tomorrow.

361
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Interview?

362
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Yeah. Tomorrow. And I'm 100% sure you'll get this job.

363
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Good.

364
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Alright, if you're so sure... I'll be there.

365
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Okay. Good. See you tomorrow.

366
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Oh, wow... What a surprise!

367
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Good morning.
-Good morning.

368
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
How'd you get my pictures?

369
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
If I could get your number... Getting your pictures is no big deal.

370
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Don't take me wrong.

371
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It's my job.

372
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Telling people who have no idea their true worth.

373
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And, believe me, you're worth it.

374
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Please, take a seat.

375
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Thank you.

376
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Tea or coffee?

377
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
No, thanks, I'll be leaving quickly. I've got to go back.

378
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Blimey, you've barely come here and you're in a hurry to leave?

379
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Just a second.

380
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Two cups of coffee. Quick.

381
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Please shut it down, will you?

382
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
By the way... I like your personality.

383
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why did you want to meet me?

384
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Malika... As pretty and proud as your name...

385
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That's a good one!

386
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm serious.

387
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I knew the moment I saw your pictures that the camera will fall in love with you.

388
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You could be the next superstar in modelling or TV.

389
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What happened? Why so nervous?

390
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I can't get into what you're talking about.

391
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Just one photoshoot.

392
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That's all it takes to change your fate.

393
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I won't be allowed to.

394
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Who do you need to ask?

395
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Family or someone else?

396
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I mean, you're so lovely... You must have a boyfriend.

397
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Or a lover whose happiness means the world to you.

398
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Yeah, right.

399
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Think again.

400
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm sure he can't help you live out the kinds of dreams I can.

401
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
That's right, but...

402
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I don't want this to drive a wedge between us.

403
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And if I promised that nothing of the sort will ever happen?

404
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Keep it here.

405
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Thank you.

406
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You happened to come when I was looking for a fresh face.

407
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
For an international brand.

408
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Imagine the exposure...

409
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Imagine, that's your first chance.

410
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It's just like a dream come true for you.

411
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Okay...

412
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
If it doesn't suit you, you may leave...

413
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm really surprised, though...

414
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Why'd you come here in the first place if you had all these problems, didn't want to do it?

415
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Please, sit.

416
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Sit.

417
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Someone so lovely and beautiful as you...

418
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Couldn't possibly miss this chance!

419
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Thousands dream of this.

420
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
You're the one who gets to live the dream.

421
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I'm worried about my family.

422
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
They won't allow me.
-Don't worry about that.

423
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
No one will hear. Trust me.

424
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It's an international shoot. It isn't even for the local market.

425
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
But --
-Just a minute.

426
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Here's your advance.

427
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Think carefully.

428
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
If you said no, I'm cancelling the cheque, and if you said yes, you're getting double this amount at the end of the shoot.

429
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Think about it

430
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And let me know.

431
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Malika ain't here!

432
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
It was yous twos yesterday... Just her today...

433
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What's up, mate?

434
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
No idea about today. She did text she's busy.

435
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
And yesterday?

436
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Where were you two?

437
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
No secrets from friends!

438
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I swear it wasn't planned!

439
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Now you're suckin' diesel!

440
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
So, did you say it?

441
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Obviously, they wouldn't have just stared at each other.

442
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
C'mon!

443
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
So did you tell her your secret?

444
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Did you?
-So?

445
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Did you tell her?

446
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
I couldn't talk about it.

447
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Worried she'd leave you if she found out?

448
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
She loves me, she can't just leave me!
-Go and tell her, then.

449
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
What's your problem?
-Jeez! Be done with it!

450
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Tell him to watch what he's saying!
